    "For random, comparisons are randomly selected from the set of all possible comparisons.",
    "For no-repeat, if (x i, x j) is selected then (x j, x i) will not be selected.",
    "For symmetric, if (x i, x j) is selected, then (x j, x i) will also be selected.",
    "Given a set of selected comparisons C and weights of a comparative assessment system θ, one can generate a predicted rank ordering r1:N of the candidate responses.",
    "A simple but effective approach is to sort the candidates by win-loss ratio,"
